  "elapsed_s": 8.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "But-- personally.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 6 SECONDS]",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And then at school, also one time I found in my pocket a sort of a train-- train ticket.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And it said, one-way ticket to Palestine.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I mean, that means, go to Palestine, you know?",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And other arguments all the time, you know, about politics also, and about Jews.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And anything specific, [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] I really don't recall.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But, yeah, my uncle, who went to the same school, the-- my father's brother, he, he-- my father told me that often he came from school with broken eyeglasses because he had to fight with-- with other students that harassed him as a Jew.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So he really felt it.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And-- so it was before the First World War.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And, well, afterwards, of course, politics changed, you know, after the First World War.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And the-- Germany became a republic, a democratic republic.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So-- and the, as I-- as I said before, the Democrats were mostly not antisemitic.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And the working class was not.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And they were the majority in, in the republic-- at first.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But afterwards, of course, because of the-- of the economic deterioration after the First World War, the Nazis were founded in the first place.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And then because of the economic [PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] distress, you know, and, and unemployment, very high unemployment and enormous-- I mean, astronomic inflation, you know-- when the money completely lost its value and people lost their savings all because of the war, the First World War, which-- which Germany started.",
      "word_count": 52
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So the Nazis really grew.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And more and more antisemitism grew with it because it was always a very effective means of, of [PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] getting the support of many citizens for, for the nationalistic parties.",
      "word_count": 33
    }
  ],
